Sprint 1 plan:

Step 1: create github repository and add members
Step 2: create files : ReadME, meeting minutes, code
Step 3: Make a google docx and come up with user stories, task breakdowns for core features
Step 4: Brainstorm extra features and make user stories and task breakdowns for them.
Step 5: Make github issues with Core features and sub issues for their features and write proper user stories and task breakdowns in each one.
Step 6: Assign priorities to user stories and tasks.
Step 7: Add Scrum MAster to github
Step 8: Issue commits and ask team members for review.
Step 9: Assign some pull requests / issues to members to work on them.
